<strong>If you would like to cancel an order</strong>, please contact us as soon as possible, as orders are transferred to our warehouse immediately.<br /><br />
<strong>If you have received your order and changed your mind on the purchase</strong>, then in line with the Distance Selling Regulations (DSR) you can do so, provided you inform us of your decision within 30 days of receiving the order.<br /><br />
All customers have a legal right to return an order within seven days of receipt of the order, however, Racquet Depot UK has extended this guarantee to 30 days. The product must not be used and must be ''as new'' when returned to us.<br /><br />
Once you have informed us that you wish to return goods under the DSR, you have 28 calendar days to do so, at your own expense.<br /><br />
Once the product is received at our warehouse, we will issue a full refund for the product to your original payment method, <u>minus the true cost of initially sending out the product(s).</u><br /><br />
<strong>If an order arrives damaged</strong>, we ask that you report issues with delivery within 24 hours of receipt. If the products are visibly damaged on receipt, pictures should be taken immediately in order for us to make a claim with the shipping provider.<br /><br />
At the request of Royal Mail and all couriers, you must not have any further contact with the box or products, in order to avoid the possibility of an accusation of tampering.<br /><br />
<strong>If a product is faulty</strong>, you have 28 calendar days in which to inform us of any original fault. After this period, any applicable warranty commences.<br /><br />
