<div id="tab4Content" style="display:none" class="tabtext"><h3>What if I have received my parcel, but they were not the goods ordered?</h3>

<p>Mistakes are rare, but they do happen. In the unlikely event that we have sent you the incorrect goods, then first of all we apologise. We want to make sure that we rectify this as soon as possible and ensure that we get the goods you ordered to you. In this event, please contact Customer Services by email <a href="mailto://enquiries@milletsports.co.uk">enquiries@milletsports.co.uk</a> where one of our advisors will be happy to assist you. Customers must always send back their order with an accompanying returns form - this will ensure we can process your return quickly.</p>
<p>*(i.e where there is no legal right to a refund or exchange under the Distance Selling Regulations or otherwise)</p>

<h3>How do I know when my order has been dispatched?</h3>
<p>When we dispatch your order we will send you an email to let you know, containing information on the products dispatched to you. </p>

<h3>Why did I receive some items but not others I ordered?</h3>
<p>Whenever possible, we dispatch all of your items together. However, sometimes we might be waiting for stock and rather than keep you waiting for all of your goods (particularly if they are unrelated), we may dispatch the items we have in stock to you and then send any other items when we receive them. You will not incur additional delivery charges if we do this.</p>
<p>If you inform us that you want all of the items together or if we can tell that you need all of the items together (for instance if you have ordered a table tennis table and some bats) then we will not dispatch your order unless it is complete.</p>

<h3>What do I do if I receive a faulty product?</h3>
<p>We have high standards at Millet Sports and only source products from high quality brands and suppliers. Most items sold on our website have a full manufacturer''s warranty. If any product we supply fails prematurely due to a manufacturing defect we will be happy to assist you in providing a replacement or alternative product. However, due to the highly technical nature of many of our products, ahead of providing a replacement or alternative product, we are required to send all faulty products to the manufacturer for expert analysis. Please note this can take up to 28 days, however faulty items are normally replaced much quicker. In the event the manufacturer deems the product is not faulty, and damage was caused by mis-use, unfortunately we are not able to replace the item or offer an alternative. Please follow our easy returns process if you have a faulty item and we will be happy to assist you.</p>
<p>In the event that the product is deemed faulty on first inspection, and ahead of first use, please notify us (within 14 days of receipt), we will arrange a replacement immediately. Once the product has been used, all faults come under manufacturer''s warranty and are bound by the process listed above. Please follow our easy returns process listed if you have a faulty item and we will be happy to assist you.</p>

<h3>Where do you deliver to?</h3>

<p>We choose our couriers to ensure that we have a wide geographical coverage for deliveries. This means that we deliver to over 100 countries around the globe. For more information about what countries we deliver to and the likely charges, please visit our International delivery tab. For further information on Australian delivery please visit our  Australian Delivery tab.</p>

<h3>How long will my Australian delivery take?</h3>

<p>We aim to get all orders delivered within 5 – 14 days, however the majority of parcels will arrive in 7 days. We will tell you when we have dispatched your order so you will know when to expect it. Please note that some items that need to be ordered specially and may take a little longer.</p>

<h3>How long will my International delivery take?</h3>
<p>We aim to get all orders delivered as quickly as possible, and work with a number of established and trusted couriers to ensure this happens. For more information on delivery times and costs, please see our International Delivery tab. We will tell you when we have dispatched your order so you will know when to expect it. Most International orders will have a tracking number, which will be sent to you with your dispatch confirmation. You will be able to track these using the links on the delivery page. If your parcel was dispatched using Royal Mail Airmail, we may have to wait up to 28 days after dispatch to track your parcel.</p>

<h3>Can I cancel my order?</h3>
<p>Yes you can, if you realise you do not wish to keep an item then you can cancel anytime up to 7 days after you receive your order (starting the day after you received them) by informing us in writing. If you wish to cancel an order before we have dispatched it then please email us as soon as possible. </p>


<h3>How do I return an order?</h3>
<p>If you wish to return an order to us as a result of cancelling an order, making an exchange or if there is a problem please follow the returns process. </p>

<h3>How long will it take to get my refund?</h3>
<p>We aim to process your refund within 3 working days of receiving your goods back and you will get an email to let you know when we have processed it. We will refund the amount to the card you used to place the order and once we have processed it, you may need to allow another 5-10 days for the refund to appear credited back to your account depending on which card issuer or bank you are with.</p>

<h3>Do you have size guides?</h3>
<p>Yes we do, because lots of our brands and suppliers have subtle differences in their sizing so you''ll find them where it most makes sense, on the product pages. Just look beneath the main product image and you''ll see a little tab marked ''Size guide'', click on this and an overlay will launch showing you all the information you need in a table.</p>

<h3>Dont have my size on the eBay listing ?</h3>
<p>We can only sell the sizes which are available on the eBay listing. Sizes can come back into stock so please do recheck the listing for updates.</p>

<h3>Can you send my items as a "Gift" on the customs form?</h3>

<p>At Millet Sports all our order processing and despatch systems are automated we cannot detail your item as a gift on the customs label. </p>

<h3>Contact </h3>
<p>Our team of experienced customer service colleagues are here to help, weather you want to place an order, get product advice or require post sales assistance just email <a href="mailto://enquiries@milletsports.co.uk">enquiries@milletsports.co.uk</a></p>
</div>
<div id="tab5Content" style="display:none" class="tabtext"><p>To return items ordered from eBay, please email us at <a href="enquiries[at]milletsports.co.uk">enquiries[at]milletsports.co.uk</a> detailing the items you want to return, and reason. We will then send you an authorisation form which must be included with your return to our in country hub. Ahead of emailing us, please ensure you have read the returns T&amp;C’s below.</p>
<p>We try to ensure that all our goods are exactly what you want and reach you in good condition, however, if you do need to return anything to us please read our policy below. For a goodwill refund or exchange* items must be unused and returned in the original packaging and in a re-saleable condition within 21 days of receipt of your goods. On receipt of your item we will process your return and process the refund within 48 hours.</p>
<p style="color:#FF0000">Please ensure you have completed the process above and received authorisation for your return. Failure to do so may result in a delay and/or your item not being accepted for a return.</p>
<h3>Exchanges/Unacceptable Returns &amp; Faulty items</h3>
<h2>Exchanges</h2>
<p>Should you wish to exchange the item for an alternative size/colour etc. please complete the returns process above to obtain a refund, and place a separate order for the required item.</p>

<h3>Unacceptable Returns</h3>
<p>Unacceptable returns are classed as returns that are not in their original condition, without the original packaging and without the labels attached. We would suggest if you have purchased shoes or clothing and are trying them on for size, you try them on in a clean environment and not outside, so as not to dirty the product in any way. If you return an item to us outside of the terms of our returns policy and your statutory rights do not apply we may not refund you. The item may be returned to you at your expense and you will be notified of this and any other charges. If you choose to send the item back to us again, or refuse to accept delivery, this will be deemed as an irreversible instruction for us to dispose of your goods without further notice. This will not constitute any admission that we have failed to honour, our obligations to you in full and will not constitute any unlawful action against the goods.</p>

<h3>Faulty Items</h3>
<p>In the event of receiving a faulty or wrongly sent item, please email us at <a href="mailto://enquiries@milletsports.co.uk">enquiries@milletsports.co.uk</a> to let us know and we''ll take you through the faulty returns process, which will advise you on how to send the item back to us. In the event that the item is sent back to us without contacting us first, we may not be able to refund your return postage. Faulty items should be returned within a reasonable time and in a clean and dry condition. Please ensure the form below is completed in full. Your statutory rights are not affected.</p>

<h3>Cancelling an order</h3>
<p>If you wish to cancel please inform us by email quoting your order number at <a href="mailto:enquiries@milletsports.co.uk">enquiries@milletsports.co.uk</a>. </p>

